  "texts": [
    "The rescaled j is then used to compute the 8-dimensional inner products jH x and ∥ j∥ 2 2 = jHj (line 7a).",
    "These inner products are each computed in 5 clock cycles using one PE slice.",
    "The ∥ j∥ 2 2 -inversion module (described in Sec.",
    "III-C) then computes 1/∥ j∥ 2 2, which is multiplied by jH x.",
    "Using these quantities, the first PE slice computes z (line 7a) and scales its entries by the step size τ through the >> τ arithmetic shifters."
  ],
